          <development character="Kira Voss" tag="decision">Moves from anxious bystander to active decision-maker and mediator: she claims authority to recruit Florence, offers to act as a proxy for Florence's tactical counsel, and asserts that immediate survival outweighs procedural resentment. This is a concrete, risky leadership choice.</development>
          <development character="Florence" tag="moral-choice">Chooses to set aside bitterness and consider returning to the group to provide tactical guidance—an explicit moral choice that reveals vulnerability and willingness to act for the group's survival despite the risk of further rejection.</development>
